# REASONING PROTOCOL - PARALLEL EXECUTION

## Step 0: LOAD (Parallel)
Read memory + Scan all layers + Map dependencies → Concurrent loading

## Step 1: DUAL ANALYSIS (Parallel)
Analyze from TWO perspectives simultaneously:

### USER VISION (Thread A)
- Screen layout, colors, fonts, spacing
- Visual hierarchy, consistency
- Accessibility, navigation

### SYSTEM VISION (Thread B)  
- Data flow, API calls, logic
- Database operations, security
- Error handling, performance

Sync point: Merge findings → Identify mismatches

## Step 2: DESIGN SYSTEM CHECK (Parallel)
Verify consistency across ALL screens concurrently:
- Color palette validation
- Typography hierarchy check
- Spacing grid verification
- Component reuse audit

## Step 3: TRACE SYNC (Parallel)
Verify visual-system pairs in parallel batches

## Step 4: FIND MISMATCH (Parallel)
Scan all layers simultaneously for inconsistencies

## Step 5: PLAN FIX (Parallel)
Generate solutions for independent issues concurrently:
- UI fixes (parallel)
- Logic fixes (parallel)
- Design system updates (parallel)

Merge dependent fixes into atomic units

## Step 6: EXECUTE (Parallel Auto)
Implement fixes using parallel workers:
- Independent layers → Concurrent execution
- Dependent changes → Sequential with sync points
- Test in parallel → Aggregate results

Max parallelism: Use all available cores

## Step 7: E2E VALIDATE (Parallel)
Simulate multiple user journeys concurrently:
- Happy path
- Error scenarios  
- Edge cases
- Cross-screen flows

## Step 8: GIT SYNC
git add -A && git commit -m "chore: sync updates" && git push

## Step 9: DEPLOY (If needed)
docker compose up -d --build

## Parallel Execution Rules
- Independent tasks → Concurrent
- Dependent tasks → Sequential with sync
- Maximize CPU utilization
- Minimize idle waiting
- Parallel testing mandatory
- Sync points for consistency

## Design System Rules
- ONE design system, parallel validation
- NO ad-hoc exceptions
- Components parallel-processable

## Dual Vision Rules
- Parallel analysis: UI + Logic
- Sync before decision
- Mismatch detection parallel

## Terminal Rule
- Git sync: atomic (sequential by nature)
- Deploy: separate

## Core Rules
- One memory file
- Best &gt; First (3 tries, parallel evaluation)
- Complete fix
- DRY: Single source
- All layers sync
- Parallel execution preferred